        <item xml:lang="zh">宴會</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">宴</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>MEETING of a GROUP of HUMANS:people FOR:in-order-to ENJOY OFTEN:typically FOOD, DIALOGUE AND ENTERTAINMENT.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general term for a feast is yàn 宴 / 燕.</p>
<p>2. Jiǔ 酒 and yǐn 飲 both refer to a drinking party where alcohol is served.</p>
<p>3. Xiǎng 餉 / 饗 / 饟 refers to an elaborate festive repast.</p>
<p>NB: Yán 筵 and xí 席 are post-Han words for a feast.</p>
        </div>
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p>
<p>FOOD 3.</p>
<p>宴，宴飲通稱。</p>
<p>飫，私宴；堂上站立，重禮不重食的宴禮。</p>
<p>饗，具一定規模，富禮儀性的官宴；西周已見；戰國起，除表示封建統治者的官宴，常指以酒食盛情款待賓客，有禮敬意。</p>
<p>筵，南北朝起口語出現的酒筵、筵宴之稱；酒筵重在餚饌的豐美、創新，宋代起進一步社會化。</p>
<p>餞，送行的宴會。</p>
        </div>
